<title>Machaut: Le Jugement du Roi de Navarre</title>
</head><body>
<h2>Machaut: Le Jugement du Roi de Navarre</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Le Jugement du Roi de Navarre</dt>
<dd>Machaut: Ballades, motets, virelais et textes dits<br>
Ensemble Gilles Binchois - Dominique Vellard<br>
<i>Cantus 9626</i></dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<li>Chanson roial: Joie, plaisance et douce nourriture (fiddle,
gittern, recorder, percussion)</li>
<li>Ballade: Tres douce dame que j'aour (voice, harp)</li>
<li>Poem: Un po apres le temps d'autonne</li>
<li>Motet: Plange regni / Tu qui gregem tuum ducis (4 voices)</li>
<li>Poem: Et tout einsi com je cuidoie</li>
<li>Motet: O livoris feritas / Fons totius superbie (3 voices)</li>
<li>Poem: Et quant Nature vit ce fait</li>
<li>Virelai: Puisque ma dolour (fiddle, flute, gittern)</li>
<li>Poem: Si que ces tempestes cesserent</li>
<li>Messe de Nostre Dame: Kyrie (4 voices)</li>
<li>Poem: Si que tres bien me confessay</li>
<li>Virelai: J'aim sans penser (fiddle, rebec, gittern, bagpipe,
percussion)</li>
<li>Ballade: Esperance qui m'asse&uuml;re (2 voices)</li>
<li>Ballade: Quand These&uuml;s / Ne quier veoir (4 voices)</li>
<li>Poem: Damoiselle, la tra&iuml;son de These&uuml;s</li>
<li>Ballade; 2-part arr., <a href="hmu11354.htm">Faenza Codex</a>:
Honte, paour doubtance (2 recorders)</li>
<li>Poem: Adont commensa Souffissance</li>
<li>Ballade: Nes que on porroit les estoilles nombrer (3 voices)</li>
<li>Poem: Quant leur consaus fu affinez</li>
<li>Ballade: Amours me fait d&eacute;sirer (voice, flute, fiddle)</li>
</ol></p>

<p>Performers: Anne-Marie Lablaude (voice), Brigitte Lesne (voice,
harp, percussion), Akira Tachikawa (voice), Dominique Vellard
(voice, gittern), Emmanuel Bonnardot (voice, fiddle, rebec), Pierre
Hamon (recorders, flute, bagpipes), Randall Cook (fiddle, recorder),
Jean-Paul Racodon (recitation)</p>

<p>Playing time: 65'</p>

<p>Recording date: October, 1994 (Eglise de Grancey le Ch&acirc;teau,
C&ocirc;te-d'Or, France) for Harmonic; CD issued on Cantus in
1998</p>

<p>Compilation:<br>
<a href="brl94217.htm">Brilliant classics 94217</a> [CDx3 + CD-ROM]
Guillaume de Machaut c1300-1301: Sacred and Secular Music
</p>

<p>Excerpts:<br>
[1], [12], [16] <a href="can9705.htm">Cantus C 9705/6</a> Dictionary
of Medieval &amp; Renaissance Instruments
</p>

<p>Although it does not date from the same recording session as
the renowned <a href="har8825.htm">Le vray rem&egrave;de d'amour</a>
program, this is a recording made by Harmonic which did not make
it into distribution at the time.  It has finally been released
on Cantus in lavish packaging and with ample documentation.</p>

